# Trivy CVE/GHSA allowlist for this repo. Every entry must have a comment
# explaining why it can't be fixed via requirements.txt/Dockerfile, so this
# file stays an audit trail, not a place vulnerabilities go to be forgotten.

# json_repair 0.25.3 (HIGH, unbounded-CPU DoS via circular JSON Schema $ref)
# in agent-service. crewai's entire 1.x line (no 2.0.0 release exists yet)
# exactly-pins json-repair~=0.25.2, and no patched release exists inside
# that range (json-repair jumped straight from 0.25.3 to 0.60.0 with no
# 0.25.x backport). Forcing a newer json-repair makes pip's resolver fail
# outright (ResolutionImpossible) rather than install anything at all, so
# this is a real upstream constraint, not a pin we chose. Re-check this
# entry whenever crewai's requirements.txt line is bumped — if a future
# crewai release loosens the json-repair constraint, remove this line and
# let Trivy's gate re-block until requirements.txt actually points at a
# patched version.
GHSA-xf7x-x43h-rpqh
